<p><b>Sardinian</b> (<b>Sardu</b>, <b>Limba Sarda</b>) is the collective name of the <a href="/wiki/Vernacular" title="Vernacular">vernacular</a> linguistic varieties spoken in most of the island of <a href="/wiki/Sardinia" title="Sardinia">Sardinia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Italy" title="Italy">Italy</a>. It is considered the most conservative of the <a href="/wiki/Romance_languages" title="Romance languages">Romance languages</a> in terms of <a href="/wiki/Phonology" title="Phonology">phonology</a> and is noted for its <a href="/wiki/Paleosardinian_language" title="Paleosardinian language" class="mw-redirect">Paleosardinian</a> <a href="/wiki/Substratum" title="Substratum" class="mw-redirect">substratum</a>.</p>
